WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:27.460
Let's go!

00:30.000 --> 00:37.000
This week we have a really exciting exercise for mental strength in the

00:37.000 --> 00:42.080
horses and the connection between horse and rider. So there's a lot of variations

00:42.080 --> 00:47.400
to this exercise but the point of the matter is to put your horse through two

00:47.400 --> 00:54.600
three four different shapes right in a row and you're looking for responsiveness

00:54.760 --> 01:00.280
connection and reaction time on both your part and the ability to follow a

01:00.280 --> 01:09.240
pattern quickly and concisely. So don't worry too much about the quality of each

01:09.240 --> 01:14.480
movement until you've done the pattern a bunch of times and maybe you've done

01:14.480 --> 01:19.640
you're gonna do this exercise multiple times this week. So each movement is

01:19.640 --> 01:24.320
gonna be start out simple and you can make it more advanced as you get better

01:24.320 --> 01:30.840
and better and better at it. And to explain it I've brought you an Etsy

01:30.840 --> 01:40.960
sketch. So first off we have a leg yield towards the center line and then we're

01:40.960 --> 01:46.160
gonna travel straight up the center line and start making a circle between 10 and

01:46.160 --> 01:51.320
15 meters based on your ring. Then we're gonna travel back down the long side in

01:51.320 --> 01:57.280
full straightness. Make a corner according to your horse's level and

01:57.280 --> 02:03.160
across the short side and repeat. So we're gonna leg yield in this case right

02:03.160 --> 02:12.680
and then travel up the center line the same. Circle left 10 to 15 meters based

02:12.680 --> 02:18.320
on your ring size and your horse's ability and then travel down the long

02:18.320 --> 02:24.520
side and in conclusion you can go across the short side and repeat.

02:28.880 --> 02:33.200
So starting with our leg yield you want to remember the leg yield needs to be

02:33.200 --> 02:38.120
more forward than it is lateral and the horse should be leading with its shoulder

02:38.120 --> 02:43.560
going across that leg yield and if you ever lose your forward you need to fix

02:43.600 --> 02:49.280
that first. When you're traveling up the center line think of two train tracks or

02:49.280 --> 02:54.960
two walls on either side of your arms to keep you very straight. As you make your

02:54.960 --> 02:59.080
circle the curvature of the horse should represent the size and the shape of the

02:59.080 --> 03:03.720
circle that you've chosen. So don't make your curve in your horse too great or

03:03.720 --> 03:08.440
too small based on the circle. As you begin to travel straight down the long

03:08.480 --> 03:14.240
side use the wall to help you guide your straightness in head, neck, shoulders, hips,

03:14.240 --> 03:22.640
lumbar. An alternate route for this same exercise would be to work on one

03:22.640 --> 03:27.400
direction at a time. Leg yield across the center line, straight over the center

03:27.400 --> 03:34.480
line, circle right and then travel across the diagonal. This is a great way to help

03:34.520 --> 03:39.240
your horse go forward across the diagonal if they need a slight mental

03:39.240 --> 03:46.720
break and then you can repeat the same side twice or three times. This alternate

03:46.720 --> 03:51.600
pattern is best done in the walk and the trot because of the same sidedness

03:51.600 --> 03:56.960
direction unless you are sufficient in counter canter. You can also accelerate on

03:56.960 --> 03:59.680
the diagonal.

